<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=6769&amp;p=29848#p29848"><![CDATA[
If you want more background images, you can simply make many beautiful background images by yourselves thanks to a great software abstractcurves.<br /><br />Whose offical website is: <!-- m --><a class="postlink" href="http://abstractcurves.com/">http://abstractcurves.com/</a><!-- m --><br /><br />Here is a simply guidence on how to make a background images with a few clicks.<br /><br />First, launch abstractcurves and click new image.<br /><img src="http://i65.tinypic.com/abme76.jpg" alt="" /><br /><br />Then, a windows will pop out for you to choose size, transparecy and so on. The recommend background image size is 700*1400, but if you are using a high dpi monitor you should set the size a little lager so that the images will not show repeatedly.<br /><img src="http://i63.tinypic.com/jkc2sx.jpg" alt="" /><br /><br />Here goes the main windows. Here is a very simple introduction of the basic features. If transparent background opion is enabled, the back ground image will behave like Twister alpha only. Use a custom dark color.png made by juniper7.<br /><img src="http://i67.tinypic.com/110zj9h.jpg" alt="" /><br /><br /><br /><img src="http://i66.tinypic.com/dxjzmr.jpg" alt="" /><p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=14569">shpkong</a> — Sat Oct 15, 2016 10:52 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
