Wonderful shpkong.<br /><br />I have menu envy now.<br /><br /><br />You beat me to it. Time for me to retire. <br />I was working on a similar skin that would have Ivo's wavy ripple textured image,<br />from his &quot;metallic&quot; skin' with transparency at same time.<br />Got 3/4 there, was working ok on Win 10, then gave up when I tried on Win7.It was terrible. Colors were so weak. <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_sad.gif" alt=":(" title="Sad" /><br /><br />Using your skin, I can just add the same custom image, and it is so easy.<br />You found the way to do it, by having the picture in the alpha channel of image.<br /><br />It looks like you got the same problem, as I got, with the search box not showing properly.<br />Sometimes it looks ok, other times shows the grey part. See picture.<br />I tried everything then went back to look at &quot;Metallic&quot; skin. <br />It has something to do with using the <br />Search_pattern_mask, Search_pattern_search_mask and Search_pattern_jump_mask <br /><br />You need to for sure add the first one Search_pattern_mask=<br />Once that red/ black bitmap is added, along with the text, search box will be white 100% of the time. <img src="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/images/smilies/icon_e_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" /><br /><br />I did notice what you were talking about with the round corners, and pixels a different color.<br />They are showing color bleed through. <br />Only way to get rid of them is edit the red bitmap so red pixels are max on, or totaly off black.<br /><br />Excellent work shpkong.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=856">juniper7</a> — Wed Sep 14, 2016 1:40 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
